Add port() method to Actor base class enabling 1:N broadcasting via named channels.

API Design:
```typescript
interface Actor {
  // Existing
  receive(msg: Message): Promise<MessageResponse>;

  // New
  port(name: string): Channel<Event> & Disposable;
}
```

Implementation:
1. Add port() method signature to Actor base class
2. Each port is a child actor managing subscriber list
3. Returns AsyncIterable<Event> with Disposable for cleanup
4. Support backpressure per-subscriber (independent buffers)
5. Auto-cleanup on actor shutdown

Example usage:
```typescript
class SessionActor extends Actor {
  port(name: 'state-changes' | 'errors'): Channel<Event> {
    return this.createPort(name);
  }
}

// Consumer
using changes = sessionActor.port('state-changes');
for await (const event of changes) {
  updateUI(event);
}
```

