Create comprehensive demo showcasing Widget Actors in a real chat application.

Demo Components (Widget Actors):
1. <chat-room> - Room container, manages session
2. <chat-message> - Individual message component
3. <chat-input> - Message composition widget
4. <user-list> - Connected users sidebar

Actor Patterns Demonstrated:
- Point-to-point messaging (input → room)
- Broadcasting via ports (room.port('messages') → all message widgets)
- Signal-to-channel bridges (DOM events → actor messages)
- Integration with backend SessionActor (future)

Example Architecture:
```typescript
class ChatRoom extends ActorMixin(HTMLElement) {
  private messages = signal<Message[]>([]);
  private users = signal<User[]>([]);

  async receive(msg: Message): Promise<MessageResponse> {
    switch (msg.type) {
      case 'send-message':
        this.messages.set([...this.messages.get(), msg.payload]);
        return { success: true };

      case 'user-joined':
        this.users.set([...this.users.get(), msg.payload]);
        return { success: true };
    }
  }

  port(name: 'messages' | 'users'): Channel<Event> {
    if (name === 'messages') return signalToChannel(this.messages);
    if (name === 'users') return signalToChannel(this.users);
  }

  connectedCallback() {
    super.connectedCallback();
    effect(() => this.render()); // agentic-ui pattern
  }
}

class ChatInput extends ActorMixin(HTMLElement) {
  port(name: 'user-input'): Channel<Event> {
    if (name === 'user-input') {
      return domEventChannel(this.querySelector('button'), 'click');
    }
  }

  async send() {
    const room = actorRegistry.lookup(address('chat-room-main'));
    await actorRegistry.send(
      address('chat-room-main'),
      { type: 'send-message', payload: { text: this.input.value } }
    );
  }
}
```

