Create unified Channel<T> interface that encompasses streaming, ports, and future duplex patterns.

Three Channel Patterns:
1. StreamChannel<T> - Point-to-point (1:1) via streamAsync()
2. PortChannel<T> - Pub/sub (1:N) via actor.port()
3. BridgeChannel<T> - External systems (DOM events, WebSockets)

Proposed Interface:
```typescript
interface Channel<T> extends AsyncIterable<T>, Disposable {
  // Core iteration
  [Symbol.asyncIterator](): AsyncIterableIterator<T>;

  // Optional sending (for duplex)
  send?(value: T): Promise<void>;

  // Lifecycle
  close(): void;
  readonly closed: boolean;

  // Observability
  readonly buffered: number;

  // Cleanup
  [Symbol.dispose](): void;
}

interface ChannelOptions {
  bufferSize?: number;
  signal?: AbortSignal;
  onBackpressure?: (isPaused: boolean) => void;
}
```

Implementation Strategy:
1. Create base Channel<T> interface in src/messaging/channel.ts
2. StreamChannel wraps existing streamAsync() implementation
3. PortChannel implements multicast with per-subscriber buffers
4. BridgeChannel adapts external async sources

